sentence: (RTTNews) - The Home Depot, Inc. (HD) revealed a profit for first quarter that dropped from the same period last year.
The company's earnings totaled $2.25 billion, or $2.08 per share.
This compares with $2.51 billion, or $2.27 per share, in last year's first quarter.
Analysts had expected the company to earn $2.26 per share, according to figures compiled by Thomson Reuters.
Analysts' estimates typically exclude special items.
The company's revenue for the quarter rose 7.1% to $28.26 billion from $26.38 billion last year.

The Home Depot, Inc. earnings at a glance:

-Earnings (Q1): $2.25 Bln.
-Analysts Estimate: $2.26 -Revenue (Q1): $28.26 Bln vs. $26.38 Bln last year.
